This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with improving feature tracking in video data. The use of gyroscopes to assist in tracking also suggests that it may belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of energy functions, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with video data, which could also place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
